Package: EconomicPolarizationEU2025
Title: Reproducibility of Economic Polarization in the European Union
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
person('Jonas', 'Dominy', email = 'jonas.dominy@example.com', role = c('aut', 'cre')),
person('Claudius', 'Gräbner-Radkowitsch', role = 'ctb', comment = 'Europa-Universität Flensburg & JKU'),
person('Philipp', 'Heimberger', role = 'ctb', comment = 'Wiener Institut für Internationale Wirtschaftsvergleiche'),
person('Jakob', 'Kapeller', role = 'ctb', comment = 'Universität Duisburg-Essen & JKU')
Description:
This project reproduces the graphics and analysis of the paper
"Economic Polarization in the European Union: Development Models in the Race for the Best Location" (2025) by Jonas Dominy,
Claudius Gräbner-Radkowitsch, Philipp Heimberger, and Jakob Kapeller.
The study analyzes developmental trajectories in the EU and diagnoses economic polarization
on two levels: income divergence across countries and the emergence of heterogeneous
development models (core, periphery, workbench economies, and financial hubs).
License: MIT
